parsed.name: 3x Weekly Arm Building Program

metadata.value: Routine to prepare for upper body workouts.

exercises.notes: 5-10 minutes of arm circles, shoulder dips, torso twists, and light jogging.

exercise.name: Bicep Curl (Dumbbells)
exercise.description: Standing or seated, lift dumbbells towards shoulders, contracting the biceps.

metadata.value: Keep elbows close to the torso during the movement.

exercise.name: Tricep Dips (Bench)
exercise.description: Using a bench, lower and raise your body using your arms.

metadata.value: If needed, keep feet on floor for less intensity.

exercises.notes: Develops the triceps for balanced arm growth.

exercise.name: Hammer Curl
exercise.description: Similar to bicep curl but with palms facing each other.

exercises.notes: Enhances grip strength and overall arm development.

exercise.name: Overhead Tricep Extension (Dumbbell)
exercise.description: Holding a dumbbell with both hands, extend overhead and lower behind the head.

metadata.value: Maintain core engagement to support back.

exercises.notes: Focuses on long head of tricep for thickness.

exercise.name: Concentration Curl
exercise.description: Sitting, curl one arm at a time while resting elbow on inner thigh.

exercise.name: Cooldown Stretching
exercise.description: Static stretching focusing on the arms and shoulders after workout.

exercises.notes: Incorporate stretches for the biceps, triceps, shoulders, and chest.

parsed.notes: This beginner-intermediate program focuses on arm hypertrophy and is structured for 3 days a week. Progress by gradually increasing weights or reps as strength improves.
